1. Downscale the input image so the KSampler doesnt explode, but downscale  another  copy of the image LESS. This is specifically for the depth maps, to avoid losing detail in the  maps.

Then since we are dealing with a single image, we replicate it.  Set that  in num frames  below.

To repeat the last frame and mask set extend last frame
3.  Here  I used a simple Time feature, but you can replace this with any other feature you'd  like  (audio,  motion,   brightness, whatever) and  it will work
4. I want the whole image to be included  in the depth chamber, so I create a  mask the size of the image. You could pass in masks   of anything  here.
see  above  for additional example configuration of this node that i left behind. You can do a lot
2. Preprocess  to get the image before replicating it. We use  this later  for the  Depth Chamber as well as control nets.

0. In  this  workflow we demonstrate  a way to use FlexMaskDepthChamber, and FlexImageParallax, both introduced by my node pack. We also have a look at one of the ways to use a TimeFeature

Be sure to click the "?" icons for information  about the nodes
